  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrc="shortdesc:1;5:14" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/sort-as.dita">For elements that are sorted, the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:2;5:60" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/sort-as.dita">sort-as</xmlelement> element provides
    text that is combined with the base sort phrase to construct the effective sort phrase. The text
    can be specified in the content of the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:3;7:56" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/sort-as.dita">sort-as</xmlelement> element or in the
      <xmlatt class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlatt " xtrc="xmlatt:1;8:15" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/sort-as.dita">value</xmlatt> attribute on the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:4;8:59" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/sort-as.dita">sort-as</xmlelement> element. The
      <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:5;9:19" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/sort-as.dita">sort-as</xmlelement> element is useful for elements where the base sort phrase is
    inadequate or non-existent, for example, a glossary entry for a Japanese Kanji
    phrase.</shortdesc>
